Sports cabinet secretary Amina Mohammed has now disclosed that they were given sh498 million to construct the Jomo Kenyatta international stadium in Kisumu that will be the venue of this years madaraka day celebrations. she spoke amid conflicting figures doing round in the social media discourse over the total cost allocated for the project. many Kenyans have mocked the current appearance of the stadium compared to the initial artistic impression of the stadium after completion. willy lusige reports.